          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "An ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSConnection",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object attached to a remote ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSSocketPort",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object cannot detect when the remote port becomes invalid, even if the remote port is on the same machine. Therefore, it cannot post this notification when the connection is lost. Instead, you must detect the timeout error when the next message is sent.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSConnection",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object posting this notification is no longer useful, so all receivers should unregister themselves for any notifications involving the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSConnection",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
